I have a client like this - well, she used to be that way anyhow!!!  It would take me 1 1/2 hours to do a REGULAR fill, with polish.  It wasn't so much that I was taking longer, but she would not give me her hands until she went over each and every nail with me.  Pointing out what I consider normal "wear and tear".  She won't use her cuticle oil like she should, so she gets peeling from the undersides.  I live in the DRY DRY desert and so the oil is a must!!!  Finally, I just started taking her hand and would start working - she would try to pull it away to point out something and I just kept a firm hold!!!  LOL  And would say - I need to get working!

So one day she called and needed to move her appointment.  I had an hour I could put her in on the next day.  And she says to me "Oh, but that is only an hour, it takes you an hour and a half to do my nails".  And I said to her that yes, for some reason it does, but on all my other clients I have them in and out the door in one hour, including my pink and white clients.  From that day on - I have had her in and out in UNDER an hour!!!!  LOL

The funny thing about this client is I am the ONLY one who has ever done her nails!  Lord help her if she decides to go elsewhere!!!!  LOL

Cindy D.

